Description: The Toothpick Project is transitioning from nonprofit to a hybrid social impact business.
Full Description: This project started with the end-user in mind. Through the biocontrol of Striga with the FOXY T14 toothpick technology, their goals are to reduce labor and increase crop yield for smallholder farmers. Ultimately, this technology will: improve health through more nutritious, diversified crops (impacting both physical and mental wellbeing); increase income by providing enough yield for both family use and sale; and provide greater access to education due to this increased income. Because the vast majority of maize farmers are women, these results will also impact women's empowerment, which will be reflected in a Women's Empowerment in Agriculture Index (USAID, Feed the Future) study that evaluates independence, literacy, time use, domestic violence, land ownership, and other measures of empowerment.
Industry Groups: Agriculture and Farming, Health Care, Other, Social Impact

Full Description: LookingForSpace.com is a successful matching service for principals with extra offices in their premises and professionals looking for shared office space with amenities available for sublease or license. The company specializes in is Shared Legal Office Space - but all offices in professional organizations can be listed. Listings are tagged and searchable by location, industry or size.  The company has hundreds of success stories and testimonials from law firms and other professional firms that have rented their offices through the service.   The company is now expanding its geographic footprint to major cities throughout the U.S. after successfully establishing the marketplace in New York City, because the shared office space marketplace is underserved by the real estate brokerage community.  There is great demand for the professional real estate marketing services and help provided by the company - which allows principals to transact sublease or license transactions between themselves.
